name: Python 3.6 Build 1
body: Initial release of a Python 3.6.0 support package.

name: Python 3.5 Build 3
body:
Updated to use Python 3.5.3, and OpenSSL 1.0.2k.

Also corrects the OS identifier on non-iOS mobile platforms, strips unnecessary test packages, and ships the standard library as a zip file.

name: Python 3.5 Build 2
body: An update to the initial release, correcting problems with allowing subprocesses on macOS, and platform identification on tvOS and watchOS.

name: Python 3.5 Build 1
body:
Python 3.5.2, packaged as a framework for inclusion on Apple platforms - i.e.:
- macOS
- iOS
- tvOS
- watchOS

The downloads include frameworks for OpenSSL, BZip2 and XZ, supporting the corresponding builtin modules.
